    <h1>Blocks User Manual</h1>

    <h2>Adding a Prompt to a Block</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Click on the "Add prompt to block" button.</li>
        <li>Select a block from the available options.</li>
        <li>Select a category for the prompt.</li>
        <li>Type your desired prompt in the input field.</li>
        <li>Click the "Add" button to add the prompt.</li>
    </ol>
    <img src="/images/blocks-1.png" />
    <h2>Managing Prompts</h2>
    <p>On the "Blocks" page, you will find the following information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Transcript:</strong> This column displays the transcript of the prompt.</li>
        <li><strong>Category:</strong> This column displays the category of the prompt.</li>
        <li><strong>Block Number:</strong> This column displays the block number associated with the prompt.</li>
        <li><strong>Actions:</strong> This column allows you to remove a prompt.</li>
    </ul>
     <h2>Using the Search Bar</h2>
    <p>The search bar allows you to filter the records as you type. Simply start typing in the search bar, and the table will dynamically update to display only the matching prompts.</p>
    <img src="/images/blocks-2.png"/>
    <p>To remove a prompt:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Locate the prompt you wish to remove in the table.</li>
        <li>Click the "Remove" button in the corresponding row.</li>
        <li>A confirmation message will appear asking if you want to remove the prompt permanently.</li>
        <li>If you wish to proceed, click "OK". Otherwise, click "Cancel" to keep the prompt.</li>
    </ol>
    <img src="/images/blocks-3.png"/>
   
